title: TFM: THE FIRST MOVE
description: The session aimed to spark students' interest in AI and Machine Learning, while equipping them with the knowledge and steps to start their career in the field. The insights from industry professionals and alumni were expected to inspire students to actively engage in AI-related challenges and learning paths.

title: ML101: Dive into AI-ML Basics
description: Participants gained foundational knowledge of AI/ML concepts, understand the applications of key algorithms, and develop the confidence to implement basic machine learning projects independently.

title: From Code to Impact: Build, Train, and Deploy AI
description: Participants gained hands-on experience in building and deploying AI solutions, enhancing their technical skills in AI development, deployment, and real-world application integration.

title: AI Unplugged
description: Students gained clarity on industry expectations, pathways into the AI/ML field, and how to effectively build their portfolios. The session is expected to encourage more practical learning and informed career planning among participants.
